race.comment: JOTOPELI (4) has threatened to win in his last three and was backed into the red at St Arnaud last time. Races forward and finally draws an inside barrier. Yendall is reunited and this is a winnable assignment. IMMORTAL ROSE (8) peaks and drops back in trip from a narrow defeat at Warrnambool. She's right up to this and is likely to go close on a three-week return. STOLEN STOCK (7) was quickly back to form beaten a half length at St Arnaud. He has more to offer and can make the finish. PARKRUN (5) will be better for the two solid outings since his switch from the Archibald stable. Would need to find his best, but will get every chance from the handy barrier.
